\title{Groups}
\date{2025-05-08}
\meta{parent}{gt-index}
\meta{intro}{Groups are the atoms of symmetry. Before we can state any theorem, we need to know what a group is — a set with a binary operation that behaves like composition of reversible processes. The examples to keep in mind: integers under addition, permutations of a set, rotations of a square.}

\p{A group is a set equipped with a binary operation satisfying four axioms: closure, associativity, identity, and invertibility.}
